# Build a Solo Space Sandbox Game: Like EVE Online, But You Can Make It Alone

## Reality Check: How Big Is EVE Online?

Before we start, let's be honest about what we're building.

EVE Online was developed by **CCP Games in Iceland** and has been in continuous development for **over 20 years** (launched in 2003). It has **over 300,000 active players** and a virtual economy so complex that economists study it. Its economic complexity "far exceeds single-player strategy games."

**The good news:** People have already done this alone.

> *"Astrox Imperium is a true EVE single-player replacement. Developed by one person, still in early access, but already has enough content to keep you busy."* — Player Review

Astrox Imperium was built by **one developer** using **Godot and Blender**. If someone else can do it, **you can too**.

The X series (X3 Reunion, X3 Terran Conflict, X3 Albion Prelude) are single-player space sandbox games that are "much closer to EVE than any other game suggested." They prove this genre **absolutely works in single-player mode**.

