## Example Code: Complete Combat Loop

Here's how the game loop might look:

```java
public class GameLoop implements Runnable {
    private boolean running = true;
    private Player player;
    private List<EnemyShip> enemies = new ArrayList<>();
    private List<Projectile> projectiles = new ArrayList<>();
    private double gameTime = 0;
    private int updateRate = 60;  // updates per second
    
    public void update() {
        gameTime += 1.0/updateRate;
        
        // Update enemies
        for (EnemyShip enemy : enemies) {
            enemy.update(player.getShip());
        }
        
        // Update projectiles
        for (Projectile p : projectiles) {
            p.move();
            if (p.isOutOfBounds()) {
                p.markForRemoval();
            }
        }
        projectiles.removeIf(Projectile::isMarked);
        
        // Check collisions
        checkCollisions();
        
        // Update UI
        updateHUD();
    }
    
    public void run() {
        while (running) {
            long startTime = System.nanoTime();
            update();
            long endTime = System.nanoTime();
            long frameTime = 1000000000 / updateRate;
            if (endTime - startTime < frameTime) {
                try {
                    Thread.sleep((frameTime - (endTime - startTime)) / 1000000);
                } catch (InterruptedException e) {}
            }
        }
    }
}
```

